about = The 11th issuance in the Distinguished Americans series honors phthisiologist Edward Trudeau (1848â€“1915). This noted American physician devoted himself to researching and treating tuberculosis, a highly infectious disease that proved fatal to one in seven people in the 1880s. Artist Mark Summers created the portrait on the stamp. As reference, he used a photograph of Dr. Trudeau provided by the American Lung Association. The artist is noted for his scratchboard technique, a style distinguished by a dense network of horizontal lines etched with exquisite precision.
